items.name: SDXL Rocket raccoon (Guardians of the galaxy)
BMW M5 [SDXL]
items.description:
This LoRA will render a BMW M5 into a scene. While this was trained against SDXL 1.0, do give it a try with other model checkpoints! It continues to surprise me each time I use it with different models and combinations of LoRAs as well. So experiement with this one. I have noticed that Euler ancestral, lower guidance and steps seems to produce some of the better results. Your mileage will vary.

Definitely use v1.1 (note that I didn't name the file differently, sorry) over v1.0 as it's more accurate. The dimensions and the details are just better. However, you may find the original version to be a little nicer for illustrated or stylized effects. The first iteration was a bit more difficult to work with and I don't think it was as accurate. The difference is mostly in the captioning, I completely redid the captions for v1.1. The training was slightly different as well. You can try the older version if you like, but I think v1.1 is superior. I may put out a version 2 that is trained off even more images. Version 1 is trained based off 36 images. It is a LoHa using the Prodigy optimizer with a network rank DIM and alpha of 32.

modelVersions.name: v1.1
modelVersions.description:
Slight tweaks to the training, mostly changes with the captions to use more of a tagging approach than a descriptive sentence based caption. This seems to have greatly improved the details in the front bumper and grill of the car. However, there may be some slight drawbacks for creative freedom and illustration type images might not be as good as a trade off. After training several LoHas and comparing them, this version has the best balance and is most accurate (even though some of the other versions had twice as many steps, this one was the best for accuracy).

Future versions will likely be new major versions and include the use of more training images. For the first version, this is pretty close to final and where I was hoping to get with things.

items.description:
A commission of @Zorglub (thanks a lot for your constant support, my friend).

Abbie Cornish is an Australian actress and singer, best known for her roles in films such as Sucker Punch, Limitless (both 2011) or RoboCop (2014).

This is a 125-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Do you have a specific idea for a TI in mind? Visit my website and let me know.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (abc0rnish:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: THE LEGEND OF DRAGOON《Backgrounds》
items.description:
PS1 GAME: THE LEGEND OF DRAGOON
Trained on 111 upscaled images mostly from around the LOD community.
OST <- (for inspiration~)

  • Works for anime models and seems to work on photoreal ones - to a lesser extent.

  • No sprites included

  • Add no humans in either positive or negative or not at all- your choice

  • Blue theme (add to negative prompts at a higher weight if it's too prominent)
    (Other colored themes included in the tags: Green theme, red theme, purple theme, dark/dark theme)

While I tweaked some of the tags there was an obvious mistake I overlooked after training;
The AI tagged a town as a forest...( ･_･ )...

When adding forest to the positive prompts (and only if you want a forest but it keeps generating buildings/structures) add- building, ruins, town, city, castle, house, architecture to the negative prompts.

^ Another option: Add tree, trees or woods in the negative prompts while keeping forest (at a higher weight) in the positive for potential buildings --- lol.

When adding town, building, house, ancient ruins, etc.- try also adding - castle, city, spikes, sharp edges, vanishing point, etc. (at a higher weight like 1.2 or more) in the negative prompts- If it starts going crazy with structures.
Also can try throwing rounded corners, smooth, in the positive prompts.

  • Not really trained on the dragons/virage (tagged: monster)
    Put the weight of the lora down to (0.6 or lower) perhaps for more coherent designs; although farther from the actual design but with style incorporated.

    4k/Remastered Cinematic Cutscenes <-

items.description:
Yes! My third LoRA/LyCoris and my best one, but unlike the first two this is a true concept LyCORIS, trying to copy a game character likeness and clothing, namely Elizabeth Comstock from Bioshock Infinite, before i found my true love (Claire Redfield from RE2R) there was this girl, Elizabeth, she was and still is absolutely gorgeous, she got that goth/ vintage aesthetics, the pale skin, the dark hair, the blue eyes, i mean she is perfect!

This was a test run, i trained her on 96 images using NMKD, using an aggressive rate of 0.88 and 760 steps, i've used Blender to pose her on two different locations, DaVince Resolve to improve the DataSet quality, bonkers (that's his name) office and a generic scenebuild with a couch, but both are biased towards vintage/old style with a lot of red and wood on it, so you can expect that on your renders, honestly i'm extremly happy with the result and i was NOT expecting it to be this good, i've absolutely developed a new fetish, concept creation lol

now READ THIS, if you are using exclusively Blender/Cinema/Daz/SFM then YOU HAVE TO STOP, i know i should not tell anybody wtf they should do with their lives, but i was a ludditie like many, and let me tell you AI is the future, learn with my mistakes, hating something only makes you weaker, you have to take it head on.

What i mean by this is to adapt to AI and include it on your workflow along these softwares.

items.name: Asagumo (Kancolle)
items.description:
An experimental character LoRA of Asagumo from Kantai Collection.

Info

Training with 123 images
Followed the manual form [ [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free ],
You can access to this guide in Suggested Resources section.

Recommended set up

Sampler: Euler a, DPM family series
Sampling steps: 20 or 25+
CFG Scale: 7
CLIP Skip: 2
*Do not use [restore face] on anime character!*

LoRA Weighting: [1 - 0.8], (1 - 0.6)

Baking Step:
0. Drafting (512 x 512 res to find your desired sketch)
1. Hires fix (txt2img: 768 x 768, 768 x 512, 512 x 768, or above res)
2. inpaint (img2img: refine some unwanted effect, [Euler a] with 50+ step)
3. Upscaling (img2img: res*2 with [ControlNet Tile] & Ultimate SD upscale)

Upscaler for [Step 1 - 3]: [R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, 4x-AnimeSharp, 4x-UltraSharp]
I always skip Step 0, 2 :P

Basic prompts

FIRST UPLOAD, SO IF YOU USE THIS LORA, PLEASE POST YOUR GENERATIONS! I'D LIKE TO SEE WHERE IT COULD BE BETTER! 🙏

⚠️ SORRY FOR LARGE FILE SIZE - WILL RETRAIN AND REUPLOAD IF QUALITY IS OK

I know this most likely doesn't have any real world use case, it was meant as a proof of concept for me for now.

Tested Settings (but feel free to play around):

Width x Height: 1216 x 811

Method: Euler a

Sampling steps: 20+

CFG Scale: 5-9 (depends on prompts used)

Positive Prompt Template:
Head Texture, natural skin texture, face center, (any additional facial features), <lora:head_texturesXL_V1:1>

Negative Prompt Template:

layman work, worst quality, poorly drawn, bald, bald spot, earrings, teeth, smile, open mouth, ears covered, forehead covered, hair on forehead, bangs

Observations:

This model seems to have a tendency to make male head textures with a bald spot, so if you find that happening, try pulling the lora weight down a bit.

Alternatively, if you find the lora starts to generate normal heads (not a head texture), just bring the lora weight up. It seems to vary between 0.8 to 1 depending on the prompt you use.

I also find it's sometimes better to leave out the description of the hair, unless you really want something specific, otherwise it may generate too much hair that cover the ears.

Lora also seems to work well with DreamShaperXL if you want less humanlike generations (e.g. vampire, troll, clown, etc.).

items.name: BLACKSOULS Style
items.description:
This is the LyCORIS version of a previously released LoRA. This one came out a bit different, besides being a bit more versatile, the style is a somewhat milder and the scribbles of the original images seems to have been turned into extra details instead. Pick this or the LoRA depending on what outputs you're after.

How to use
Just prompt characters as normal. There's a lot of various monster and animal girls in the dataset so those will work fine. There are various ways to change output, Euler A (gives a more smooth look), DPM++ 2M Karras (more drawing-like look) and finally adding "3D" and/or "realistic" in negatives to push the images further towards the original style.
As usual, how well things work is in the end up to how well your model handles drawing styles.
For further prompting tips see the sample images or uploaded zip of training tags.

MISC
Trained on NAI at 512 resolution with a dataset of 192 images.
All images are untouched txt2img, no inpainting or helper embeddings used for quality transparence, e.g. - things should look even better if you do.
The training was done on a small subset of the artists images, as such the output of this LoRA is not an accurate representation neither in quality or style of the source material. Go support the artist if you want the good stuff.
